node.text: Arkansas' health secretary says between April and July infections in children jumped more than 500% and hospitalizations by nearly 270%. And the timing couldn't be worse… with the start of school around the corner. Some Arkansas parents are so worried about sending their kids to class -- especially without mask mandates -- that they're lying about their kids' ages to try to get them vaccinated. Julie Stewart is a pharmacist in Fayetteville and she says she's had to turn some of these parents away.
